                            <comment id="17195892" author="paulk" created="Tue, 15 Sep 2020 06:03:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The joint compiler now does the right thing wrt annotations only appearing in &lt;em&gt;package-info.groovy&lt;/em&gt;. Groovy allows annotations to appear on package nodes in more places, e.g. &lt;tt&gt;@Grab&lt;/tt&gt; (which has SOURCE retention) can appear on a package declaration. I didn&apos;t try to expand on what might happen if the retention wasn&apos;t SOURCE as part of this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
